#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:2
msgid "Add a new technology"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:4
msgid ""
"**Goal.** Introduce a new generation tech (e.g. ``Geothermal``) into an "
"existing scenario."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:7
msgid ""
"A tech is a row in ``tech_registry.csv`` plus rows in every per-tech "
"input file. Adding one is mostly mechanical CSV editing; no code changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:12
msgid "Steps"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:14
msgid ""
"**1. Pick a slug and register the tech.** Open "
"``examples/<scenario>/input/tech_registry.csv`` and add a row:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:22
msgid ""
"The ``tech`` column is the slug used everywhere else (no spaces, no "
"dots). The ``carrier`` is a free-form string; pick something meaningful "
"(``geothermal``, ``nuclear``, ``hydrogen``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:26
msgid ""
"**2. Add rows to every per-tech input file.** The model loads the "
"following per-tech files; each needs a row for the new tech:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:37
msgid "For example in ``tech_lifetime.csv``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:44
msgid ""
"If the new tech has time-varying availability (like solar / wind), add it"
" to ``tech_max_gen_profile.csv`` as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:47
msgid ""
"**3. Optionally: existing capacity.** If some Geothermal is already built"
" before the planning horizon starts, add it to ``tech_existing.csv``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:56
msgid ""
"**4. Optionally: expansion candidates.** To allow the optimizer to build "
"new Geothermal, add rows to ``tech_candidates.csv`` with non-zero "
"``capacity_max``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:66
msgid ""
"A missing entry means \"this combination cannot be expanded\"; "
"``capacity_max=0`` has the same effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:69
msgid "**5. Re-run.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:77
msgid "Verify"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:79
msgid "Open the output NetCDF and confirm the new tech appears:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:89
msgid "Common pitfalls"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:91
msgid ""
"**Typo in the slug.** Slugs must match exactly across all CSV files and "
"``tech_registry.csv``. The loader raises a ``KeyError`` mid- build if any"
" per-tech file is missing the new slug."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:94
msgid ""
"**Forgetting ``tech_capacity_max``.** Missing rows result in a "
"``KeyError``. Use ``inf`` for unbounded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:96
msgid ""
"**Storage techs need extra files.** If ``is_storage=True`` in the "
"registry, also populate ``storage_charge_efficiency.csv``, "
"``storage_discharge_efficiency.csv``, "
"``storage_energy_to_power_ratio.csv``, and ``storage_initial_level.csv``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how_to/add_a_technology.rst:102
msgid ""
"For hydropower (``carrier='hydro'``), see "
":doc:`add_a_cascading_hydropower_system` -- the reservoir physics adds "
"another ~10 files per tech."
msgstr ""

